The  Vice Chairman of the of Kogi State Peoples Democratic Party  Chief Kola Ojo, has been reported dead.A statement by the state Publicity Secretary of the PDP, Bode Ogunmola, in Lokoja on Wednesday said Ojo slumped and died in Lagos on Tuesday evening while playing lawn tennis. Ojo, a legal practitioner, was said to be a regular player of the game at the Sports Centre, Ogudu GRA in Lagos, where the incident happened at about 5:55pm. The statement said: “The Sports Centre was said to be about a five-minute drive to his residence within the GRA. Breaking: CBN keeps banks’ LDR at 65% “He was immediately rushed to a nearby private hospital but was pronounced dead by doctors on duty.” Ogunmola described Ojo as a “reliable pillar of the party,” adding: “He was until his death the Vice Chairman of the party in Kogi West Senatorial district. He did his best to improve the fortunes of the party.” According to him, the late Ojo joined politics after retiring from the Central Bank of Nigeria. He hailed from Okoro Gbede, Ijumu Local Government Area of the state, was married and has four children.